originalText.text: Like most, I have a fear of dentists and dental work. I went in for some tooth pain and the doctor was patient with me, talked me through the whole process. Everyone at the practice was very warm and welcoming and I felt very comfortable.

originalText.text: I had a wisdom tooth extraction here when I was still a teenager years ago which was extremely painful, the wisdom teeth hadn‚Äôt even started emerging yet and I feel I was basically pressured into it. I was given only local anesthetic injected into gums, clearly not enough, mouth was pried open extremely painfully during the entire extraction. I communicated how painful it was. Also I was given no pain medication after which was very uncomfortable, and experienced extreme swelling which I believe is due to how rough the dentist Dr. Williams was with me..My other two wisdom teeth have grown in fine so the extraction was ultimately unnecessary. The woman at the front desk was nice and my family member had a good experience here.. just don‚Äôt come here for wisdom tooth extraction.
